title: Sample MDX File
description: An example of an MDX file with various elements.

body.raw:
# Sample MDX File

This is a sample MDX file demonstrating how to mix Markdown with JSX.

## Table of Contents

1. [Introduction](#introduction)
2. [Markdown Syntax](#markdown-syntax)
3. [Embedding Components](#embedding-components)
4. [Conclusion](#conclusion)

## Introduction

MDX allows you to write JSX inside Markdown files. It’s a great way to create interactive documents and blogs.

## Markdown Syntax

You can use all the regular Markdown syntax, like:

### Lists

- Item 1
- Item 2
  - Subitem 2.1
  - Subitem 2.2
- Item 3

### Code Blocks

Here’s a JavaScript code block:

```js
const greet = (name) => {
  return `Hello, ${name}!`;
};

console.log(greet("World"));
